// JOB MIGR01A ASSIGN SYSPCH TO TAPE                                    00.00.03
* SCRATCH TAPE ON 280, LABEL AS MIGRATE ALL
MTC REW,X'280'
MTC WTM,X'280',5
MTC REW,X'280'
ASSGN SYSPCH,X'280'
EOJ MIGR01A                                                             00.00.06,DURATION 00.00.02

// JOB MIGR02   COPY/CONVERT 2311 RES11A(130) TO 2314 WRK14A(192)       00.02.48
// DLBL IJSYS01,'DOS.WORKFILE.001',0,SD
// EXTENT SYS001,WRK14A,1,1,600,300
// DLBL IJSYS02,'DOS.WORKFILE.002',0,SD
// EXTENT SYS002,WRK14A,1,1,900,300
// DLBL IJSYS03,'DOS.WORKFILE.003',0,SD
// EXTENT SYS003,WRK14A,1,1,1200,300
// DLBL IJSYSLN,'DOS.WORKFILE.LNK',0,SD
// EXTENT SYSLNK,WRK14A,1,1,1500,300
// DLBL IJSYSSL,'DOS.SYSRES.FILE.VOLUME.2',,SD
// EXTENT SYSSLB,RES11B,1,1,330,1650
// ASSGN SYS001,X'192'
// ASSGN SYS002,X'192'
// ASSGN SYS003,X'192'
// ASSGN SYSLNK,X'192'
// ASSGN SYSSLB,X'131'   RES11B PRV SLB
// OPTION LINK,NODECK,XREF,DUMP
* ASSEMBLE AND LINK CVT11RES
// EXEC ASSEMBLY
 

                                              EXTERNAL SYMBOL DICTIONARY                                     PAGE    1

CVT11RES  SD  01 001800 001E10

  LOC  OBJECT CODE    ADDR1 ADDR2  STMT   SOURCE STATEMENT                                          DOS CL3-10 03/29/70.
 
                                     41 *********************************************************************** C1R00620
                                     42 *                                                                       C1R00630
                                     43 * CREATE A 199-CYLINDER SYSRES ON A 2314 DISK VOLUME                    C1R00640
                                     44 *    * MATCHES CORGZ " NEWVOL CL=55(10),RL=77(10),SL=65(10)"            C1R00650
                                     45 *    * CORE IMAGE DIRECTORY STARTS ON CYL 0 TRACK 10 FOR 10 TRACKS      C1R00660
                                     46 *    * RELOCATABLE AND SOURCE STATEMENT DIRECTORIES ARE 10 TRACKS EACH  C1R00670
                                     47 *                                                                       C1R00680
                                     48 *  1. COPY / UPDATE AS NEEDED LIBRARY CONTROL RECORDS TO 2314           C1R00690
                                     49 *     A. CYL 0 HEAD 1 RECORD 1: CORE IMAGE STATUS                       C1R00700
                                     50 *     B. CYL 0 HEAD 1 RECORD 2: POINTER TO RELOCATABLE DIRECTORY        C1R00710
                                     51 *     C. CYL 0 HEAD 1 RECORD 3: POINTER TO SOURE BOOK DIRECTORY         C1R00720
                                     52 *     D. CYL 0 HEAD 1 RECORD 4: NOT USED (DOS/VS USED THIS FOR PROCLIB) C1R00730
                                     53 *  3. COPY $$A$IPL2 TO 2314 (CYL 0 HEAD 1 RECORD 5)                     C1R00740
                                     54 *  4. COPY CORE IMAGE LIBRARY CONTENTS FROM 2311 TO 2314                C1R00750
                                     55 *     A. RE-BLOCK EACH PHASE TO REFLECT 2314 SHORTER CIL BLOCK SIZE     C1R00760
                                     56 *     B. UPDATE DIRECTORY ENTRY FOR NEW PLACEMENT AND BLOCK COUNT       C1R00770
                                     57 *     C. FORMAT THE BALANCE OF THE CORE IMAGE DIRECTORY WITH EMPTY      C1R00780
                                     58 *        DIRECTORY RECORDS.                                             C1R00790
                                     59 *     D. FORMAT THE BALANCE OF THE CORE IMAGE LIBRARY WITH EMPTY        C1R00800
                                     60 *        LIBRARY RECORDS.                                               C1R00810
                                     61 *  5. COPY RELOCATABLE MODULE LIBRARY CONTENTS FROM 2311 TO 2314        C1R00820
                                     62 *     A. NO REBLOCKING; LIBRARY BLOCKSIZES SAME ON 2311 & 2314          C1R00830
                                     63 *     B. UPDATE DIRECTORY ENTRY FOR NEW PLACEMENT AND BLOCK COUNT       C1R00840
                                     64 *     C. FORMAT THE BALANCE OF THE RELOCATABLE DIRECTORY WITH EMPTY     C1R00850
                                     65 *        DIRECTORY RECORDS.                                             C1R00860
                                     66 *     D. NO NEED TO FORMAT THE BALANCE OF THE LIBRARY.  APPARENTLY      C1R00870
                                     67 *        MAINT AND CORGZ ALWAYS USE FORMATTING WRITES WHEN ADDING       C1R00880
                                     68 *        ITEMS TO THE RELOCATABLE LIBRARY                               C1R00890
                                     69 *  6. COPY SOURCE STATEMENT LIBRARY CONTENTS FROM 2311 TO 2314          C1R00900
                                     70 *     A. NO REBLOCKING; LIBRARY BLOCKSIZES SAME ON 2311 & 2314          C1R00910
                                     71 *     B. UPDATE DIRECTORY ENTRY FOR NEW PLACEMENT AND BLOCK COUNT       C1R00920
                                     72 *     C. FORMAT THE BALANCE OF THE RELOCATABLE DIRECTORY WITH EMPTY     C1R00930
                                     73 *        DIRECTORY RECORDS.                                             C1R00940
                                     74 *     D. NO NEED TO FORMAT THE BALANCE OF THE LIBRARY.  APPARENTLY      C1R00950
                                     75 *        MAINT AND CORGZ ALWAYS USE FORMATTING WRITES WHEN ADDING       C1R00960
                                     76 *        ITEMS TO THE SOURCE STATEMENT LIBRARY                          C1R00970
                                     77 *  7. FORMAT/LOAD CYL 0 HEAD 5 THROUGH HEAD 9.  THESE ARE SPECIAL       C1R00980
                                     78 *     CORE IMAGE DIRECTORIES FOR:                                       C1R00990
                                     79 *     A.  $$ TRANSIENTS OTHER THAN $$BO TRANSIENTS (HEAD 5)             C1R01000
                                     80 *     B.  $$BO OPEN TRANSIENTS (HEAD 6)                                 C1R01010
                                     81 *     C.  $ PHASES (NOT INCLUDING $$ NOR $$BO TRANSIENTS) HEAD 7        C1R01020
                                     82 *     D.  FGP..... PHASES (MOSTLY POWER II PHASES) (HEAD 8)             C1R01030
                                     83 *     E.  CURRENTLY EXECUTING PHASE (HEAD 9)                            C1R01040
                                     84 *  8. COPY IPL BOOTSTRAP RECORDS FROM C0H0R1-2 FROM 2311 TO 2314        C1R01050
                                     85 *                                                                       C1R01060
                                     86 *  THIS PROGRAM RUNS IN AN EMULATED ENVIRONMENT, SO NO DISK ERROR       C1R01070
                                     87 *     CHECKING IS NEEDED, NOR IS IT PERFORMED.                          C1R01080
                                     88 *                                                                       C1R01090
                                     89 *  AND ALTHOUGH THE HERCULES EMULATOR SUPPORTS THE 370 INSTRUCTION      C1R01100
                                     90 *  SET, THIS PROGRAM LIMITS ITSELF TO S/360 INSTRUCTIONS.  REASONS:     C1R01110
                                     91 *                                                                       C1R01120

       CONVERT 2311 SYSRES TO 2314                                                                             PAGE    3
 
 
  LOC  OBJECT CODE    ADDR1 ADDR2  STMT   SOURCE STATEMENT                                          DOS CL3-10 03/29/70.
 
                                     92 *  1. DOS/360 DIDN'T SUPPORT THE 370 INSTRUCTIONS.  A PROGRAM CHECK     C1R01130
                                     93 *     ON A 370 INSTRUCTION COULD VERY WELL CONFUSE THE ERROR HANDLER.   C1R01140
                                     94 *  2. THIS WAS THE TOOLSET AVAILABLE TO ASSEMBLY-LANGUAGE PROGRAMMERS   C1R01150
                                     95 *     ON 360 HARDWARE.  THIS PROGRAM SERVES AS AN EXAMPLE OF HOW        C1R01160
                                     96 *     THINGS WERE DONE 'BACK IN THE DAY.'                               C1R01170
                                     97 *  3. SHOULD THERE ARISE ANOTHER EMULATOR THAT ENFORCES A S/360         C1R01180
                                     98 *     INSTRUCTION SET, THIS PROGRAM WILL BE READY TO GO.                C1R01190
                                     99 *                                                                       C1R01200
                                    100 *  EVEN THOUGH ICM, STCM, AND MVCL WOULD BE IMMENSELY USEFUL HERE.      C1R01210

       CONVERT 2311 SYSRES TO 2314   NEW SYSRES ALLOCATIONS                                                    PAGE    7
 
 
  LOC  OBJECT CODE    ADDR1 ADDR2  STMT   SOURCE STATEMENT                                          DOS CL3-10 03/29/70.
 
                                    210 *********************************************************************** C1R02310
                                    211 *                                                                       C1R02320
                                    212 * FOR SYSRES, LIBRARIES ALWAYS START ON A CYLINDER BOUNDARY.            C1R02330
                                    213 *                                                                       C1R02340
                                    214 * THE CORE IMAGE LIBRARY ALWAYS STARTS ON CYLINDER ZERO, FOLLOWED BY    C1R02350
                                    215 * THE RELOCATABLE LIBRARY (IF PRESENT) AND THEN THE SOURCE STATEMENT    C1R02360
                                    216 * LIBRARY (IF PRESENT).  A CYLINDER IS RESERVED AT THE END OF SYSRES    C1R02370
                                    217 * FOR STORAGE OF SYSTEM (GLOBAL) AND PARTITION-SPECIFIC JCL.            C1R02380
                                    218 *                                                                       C1R02390
                                    219 * THE FIRST 10 TRACKS OF THE CORE IMAGE LIBRARY ARE USED FOR SYSTEM     C1R02400
                                    220 * PURPOSES, AND THE CORE IMAGE DIRECTORY STARTS TRACK ON 10.  LIBRARY   C1R02410
                                    221 * CONTENT STARTS ON THE FIRST TRACK FOLLOWING THE CORE IMAGE DIRECTORY. C1R02420
                                    222 *                                                                       C1R02430
                                    223 * THE RELOCATABLE LIBRARY STARTS ON THE FIRST CYLINDER FOLLOWING THE    C1R02440
                                    224 * CORE IMAGE LIBRARY. THE DIRECTORY STARTS ON THE FIRST TRACK OF THAT   C1R02450
                                    225 * CYLINDER, AND LIBRARY CONTENT STARTS ON THE FIRST TRACK FOLLOWING     C1R02460
                                    226 * THE DIRECTORY.                                                        C1R02470
                                    227 *                                                                       C1R02480
                                    228 * THE SOURCE STATEMENT LIBRARY HAS THE SAME LAYOUT AS THE RELOCATABLE   C1R02490
                                    229 * LIBRARY.                                                              C1R02500
                                    230 *                                                                       C1R02510
                                    231 * PRIVATE LIBRARIES HAVE THE SAME LAYOUT AS THE CORRESPONDING SYSTEM    C1R02520
                                    232 * LIBRARY STORED ON SYSRES, INCLUDING TEN TRACKS FOR SYSTEM PURPOSES    C1R02530
                                    233 * AT THE BEGINNING OF THE CORE IMAGE LIBRARY.                           C1R02540
                                    234 *                                                                       C1R02550
                                    235 *********************************************************************** C1R02560
 
 
 
                                    237 *********************************************************************** C1R02580
                                    238 *                                                                       C1R02590
                                    239 * DEFINITIONS FOR THE NEW SYSRES TO BE BUILT ON 2314 DISK               C1R02600
                                    240 *                                                                       C1R02610
                                    241 *********************************************************************** C1R02620
 
000038                              243 R14CILCL EQU   56                  CORE IMAGE LIB CYLS, INCLUDING CYL 0 C1R02640
00000A                              244 R14CIDTK EQU   10                  CORE IMAGE DIR TRACKS, STARTS C0H10  C1R02650
                                    245 *                                  ...10 IS MIN & MAX ELSE CODE BREAKS  C1R02660

                                    265 *********************************************************************** C1R02860
                                    266 *                                                                       C1R02870
                                    267 *  DISK READ/WRITE CURSOR LAYOUT                                        C1R02880
                                    268 *                                                                       C1R02890
                                    269 *  INCLUDES CURRENT SEEK ADDRESS, ADDRESS OF DTFPH FOR I/O OPERATIONS,  C1R02900
                                    270 *  TRACK GEOMETRY, AND EXTENT INFORMATION FOR DIRECTORY OR LIBRARY      C1R02910
                                    271 *  CURRENTLY POINTED TO BY THE CURSOR.                                  C1R02920
                                    272 *                                                                       C1R02930
                                    273 *  USED TO PASS INFORMATION TO THE FOLLOWING ROUTINES                   C1R02940
                                    274 *                                                                       C1R02950
                                    275 *  XIO -      EXECUTE THE READ OR WRITE OPERATION AT THE BBCCHHR        C1R02960
                                    276 *             USING THE DTFPH POINTED TO BY THIS BLOCK                  C1R02970
                                    277 *  NXTCHR -   INCREMENT THE BBCCHHR TO THE NEXT RECORD, UPDATING TRACK  C1R02980
                                    278 *             AND CYLINDER AS NEEDED, AND INDICATING END OF EXTENT IF   C1R02990
                                    279 *             REACHED                                                   C1R03000
                                    280 *  XCHR2RBA - CONVERT CHR TO A RELATIVE BLOCK ADDRESS                   C1R03010
                                    281 *  XRBA2CHR - CONVERT RELATIVE BLOCK ADDRESS TO CHR.                    C1R03020
                                    282 *                                                                       C1R03030
                                    283 *********************************************************************** C1R03040

                                    318 *********************************************************************** C1R03390
                                    319 *                                                                       C1R03400
                                    320 * DIRECTORY/LIBRARY STATUS RECORD LAYOUT FOR DOS/360 LIBRARIES.  ALL    C1R03410
                                    321 * DIRECTORIES HAVE THE SAME STATUS RECORD LAYOUT BUT ARE STORED IN      C1R03420
                                    322 * DIFFERENT LOCATIONS.                                                  C1R03430
                                    323 *                                                                       C1R03440
                                    324 * CORE IMAGE STATUS RECORD IS CYL 0 HEAD 1 REC 1 OF SYSRES FOR A        C1R03450
                                    325 *   SYSTEM CORE IMAGE LIBRARY, AND CYL 0 HEAD 0 REC 1 OF A PRIVATE      C1R03460
                                    326 *   CORE IMAGE LIBRARY DISK EXTENT.  THE CORE IMAGE DIRECTORY ALWAYS    C1R03470
                                    327 *   STARTS ON TRACK 10 OF THE SYSRES OR PRIVATE CORE EXTENT.            C1R03480
                                    328 * SYSRES CYL 0 HEAD 0 REC 2 AND REC 3 POINT TO THE FIRST TRACK OF THE   C1R03490
                                    329 *   SYSTEM RELOCATABLE AND SOURCE SOURCE STATEMENT LIBRARY DIRECTORIES  C1R03500
                                    330 *   RESPECTIVELY.                                                       C1R03510
                                    331 * THE RELOCATABLE AND SOURCE STATEMENT LIBRARY STATUS RECORDS ARE IN    C1R03520
                                    332 *   THE FIRST 80 BYTES OF THE FIRST DIRECTORY RECORD FOR THE RESPECTIVE C1R03530
                                    333 *   LIBRARY.  EACH DIRECTORY CONTROL RECORD IN AN EMPTY LIBRARY SHOWS   C1R03540
                                    334 *   ENTRY FIVE AS THE NEXT AVAILABLE ENTRY (RELATIVE TO ZERO) TO        C1R03550
                                    335 *   SIMPLIFY THE CODE NEEDED TO SKIP OVER THE 80-BYTE (FIVE ENTRY)      C1R03560
                                    336 *   DIRECTORY CONTROL RECORD                                            C1R03570
                                    337 *                                                                       C1R03580
                                    338 *********************************************************************** C1R03590

                                    499 *********************************************************************** C1R05200
                                    500 *                                                                       C1R05210
                                    501 *  PREAMBLE.  ESTABLISH ADDRESSABILITY, OPEN FILES, READ THE LIBRARY    C1R05220
                                    502 *  POINTERS AND CONTROL RECORDS FROM THE TWO 2311 SYSRES FILES THAT     C1R05230
                                    503 *  WILL BE COPIED TO THE NEW 2314 SYSRES, AND WRITE INITIAL VERSIONS    C1R05240
                                    504 *  OF THOSE RECORDS TO THE 2314 SYSRES.                                 C1R05250
                                    505 *                                                                       C1R05260
                                    506 *  NOTE THAT $$A$IPL2, THE INITIAL IPL PROGRAM, IS ALSO READ AND        C1R05270
                                    507 *  COPIED AT THIS TIME.                                                 C1R05280
                                    508 *                                                                       C1R05290
                                    509 *********************************************************************** C1R05300
 
001800                              511 CVT11RES CSECT ,                                                        C1R05320
001800 05B0                         512 START    BALR  R11,0               ESTABLISH ADDRESSABILITY             C1R05330
001802 06B0                         513          BCTR  R11,0               BACK TO THE START ADDRESS            C1R05340
001804 06B0                         514          BCTR  R11,0                                                    C1R05350
001800                              515          USING START,R11           MAKE FIRST 4K ADDRESSABLE            C1R05360
                                    516 *                                                                       C1R05370
001806 41C0 BFFF            00FFF   517          LA    R12,4095(,R11)      SET BASE REGISTER FOR 2ND 4K         C1R05380
00180A 41C0 C001            00001   518          LA    R12,1(,R12)                                              C1R05390
002800                              519          USING START+4096,R12      MAKE SECOND 4K ADDRESSABLE           C1R05400
                                    520 *                                                                       C1R05410
                                    521 * OPEN FILES.  NOT STRICTLY NEEDED EXCEPT                               C1R05420
                                    522 *   1) TO GET A FORMAT-1 LABEL WRITTEN TO THE VTOC OF THE NEW SYSRES.   C1R05430
                                    523 *   2) TO ENABLE DISK ACCESS WHEN THE GENERATED SUPERVISOR SUPPORTS     C1R05440
                                    524 *      DASD FILE PROTECTION (SUPERVISOR GENERATION MACRO FOPT,          C1R05450
                                    525 *      DASDFP= OPERAND).  THE DISTRIBUTION SUPERVISOR DOES NOT INCLUDE  C1R05460
                                    526 *      DASD FILE PROTECTION.                                            C1R05470
                                    527 *                                                                       C1R05480
                                    528          OPEN  RES2311,SLB2311,RES2314                                  C1R05490
                                    529+* 360N-CL-453 OPEN     CHANGE LEVEL 3-3                             3-3
00180E 0700                         530+         CNOP  0,4
001810                              531+         DC    0F'0'
001810 4110 BB68            02368   532+         LA    1,=C'$$BOPEN '
001814 4500 B024            01824   533+IJJO0001 BAL   0,*+4+4*(4-1)
001818 000026F0                     534+         DC    A(RES2311)

                                    570 *********************************************************************** C1R05820
                                    571 *                                                                       C1R05830
                                    572 * CYL 0 TRACKS 5-9 WILL BE UPDATED AUTOMATICALLY BY MAINT OR CORGZ      C1R05840
                                    573 * (AND LNKEDT BUT WE'RE NOT CATALOGING ANYTHING WITH LNKEDT)            C1R05850
                                    574 * SPECIFICALLY $MAINEOJ BUT THESE 5 TRACKS NEED TO BE FORMATTED WITH    C1R05860
                                    575 * A DIRECTORY RECORD FILLED WITH BLANKS.  ONLY ONE RECORD IS NEEDED.    C1R05870
                                    576 *                                                                       C1R05880
                                    577 *   H5  TRANSIENT DIR  ($$ TRANSIENTS EXCEPT $$BO TRANSIENTS            C1R05890
                                    578 *   H6  OPEN DIR       ($$BO TRANSIENTS)                                C1R05900
                                    579 *   H7  $ PHASE DIR    (PHASES STARTING WITH '$', E.G., $JOBACCT)       C1R05910
                                    580 *   H8  FGP PHASE DIR  (PHASES STARTING WITH 'FGP' FOR FOREGROUND PGM)  C1R05920
                                    581 *   H9  CURRENT PHASE  (PHASES CREATED BY OPTION LINK FOR LOAD AND GO,  C1R05930
                                    582 *                      OR CATALOGED PHASE CURRENTLY BEING EXECUTED)     C1R05940
                                    583 *                                                                       C1R05950
                                    584 * TRACKS 5-9 ARE REBUILT IF/AS NEEDED BY $MAINEOJ                       C1R05960
                                    585 *                                                                       C1R05970
                                    586 * NOTE: THE BLANK RECORDS MUST REALLY BE EBCDIC BLANKS.  BINARY ZEROS,  C1R05980
                                    587 * AN END OF DIRECTORY MARKER ('*') OR OTHER VALUES WILL CONFUSE FETCH   C1R05990
                                    588 * IN THE SUPERVISOR AND THE SYSRES WILL NOT IPL.                        C1R06000
                                    589 *                                                                       C1R06010
                                    590 * NOTE THAT TO READ OR WRITE COUNT, KEY, AND DATA (CKD), THE SEARCH     C1R06020
                                    591 * MUST BE FOR THE RECORD PRIOR TO THE ONE TO BE WRITTEN.  TO WRITE      C1R06030
                                    592 * C0H5R1, ONE MUST SEEK C0H5R0.  FOR READ OR WRITE DATA ONLY, THE       C1R06040
                                    593 * SEARCH IS FOR THE RECORD TO BE READ OR WRITTEN (REALLY A RE-WRITE).   C1R06050
                                    594 *                                                                       C1R06060
                                    595 * AND THIS IS WHY OPERATIONS ON RECORD ZERO HAVE THEIR OWN CCW          C1R06070
                                    596 * COMMANDS.                                                             C1R06080
                                    597 *                                                                       C1R06090
                                    598 * REGISTER USAGE:                                                       C1R06100
                                    599 *    R5 = NR TRACKS LEFT TO WRITE (LOOP CONTROL)                        C1R06110
                                    600 *    R6 = CURRENT HEAD NR.                                              C1R06120
                                    601 *                                                                       C1R06130
                                    602 *********************************************************************** C1R06140
 
                                    604 *                                                                       C1R06160
                                    605 * WE COULD USE INITAREA, BUT SETTING UP THE CALLING SEQUENCE WOULD      C1R06170
                                    606 * NEARLY AS MUCH SPACE AS JUST DOING IT.                                C1R06180
                                    607 *                                                                       C1R06190
001862 9240 C178      02978         608          MVI   DIR4,C' '           MOVE A BLANK                         C1R06200

                                    611 *                                                                       C1R06230

  LOC  OBJECT CODE    ADDR1 ADDR2  STMT   SOURCE STATEMENT                                          DOS CL3-10 03/29/70.
 
                                    940 *********************************************************************** C1R09520
                                    941 *                                                                       C1R09530
                                    942 * THE SOURCE 2311 SYSRES USED FOR THIS PROGRAM INCLUDES A CORE IMAGE    C1R09540
                                    943 * LIBRARY (ALREADY COPIED) AND A RELOCATABLE LIBRARY (TO BE COPIED      C1R09550
                                    944 * IN THS SECTION).                                                      C1R09560
                                    945 *                                                                       C1R09570
                                    946 * COPY THE RELOCATABLE LIBRARY.  THIS IS MUCH SIMPLER THAN COPYING      C1R09580
                                    947 * THE CORE IMAGE LIBRARY BECAUSE THE DIRECTORY AND LIBRARY BLOCK SIZES  C1R09590
                                    948 * ARE THE SAME ON 2311 AND 2314.                                        C1R09600
                                    949 *                                                                       C1R09610
                                    950 * BUT THE DIRECTORY IS A TEENY BIT MORE DIFFICULT BECAUSE THE FIRST 80  C1R09620
                                    951 * BYTES OF THE FIRST DIRECTORY RECORD (EQUAL TO FIVE ENTRIES) IS USED   C1R09630
                                    952 * FOR THE DIRECTORY CONTROL RECORD.                                     C1R09640
                                    953 *                                                                       C1R09650
                                    954 * BECAUSE BLOCK SIZES ARE THE SAME FOR DIR AND LIBRARY, WE'LL JUST      C1R09660
                                    955 * COPY THE DIRECTORY AND THE LIBRARY BLOCK FOR BLOCK FROM THE 2311      C1R09670
                                    956 * VOLUME TO THE 2314 VOLUME.  WHILE PROCESSING THE DIRECTORY, WE'LL     C1R09680
                                    957 * RECALCULATE THE BBCCHHR FROM 2311 TO 2314 BY CONVERTING IT TO A       C1R09690
                                    958 * RELATIVE BLOCK ADDRESS FROM THE START OF THE LIBRARY AND THEN         C1R09700
                                    959 * CONVERTING THAT BACK TO THE CORRECT BBCCHHR TO 2314 TRACK GEOMETRY    C1R09710
                                    960 *                                                                       C1R09720
                                    961 * A SOURCE STATEMENT LIBRARY WILL ALSO BE COPIED, BUT THAT LIBRARY      C1R09730
                                    962 * WILL COME FROM ANOTHER SYSRES.  THE SAME DIRECTORY TRANSLATION WILL   C1R09740
                                    963 * BE DONE.                                                              C1R09750
                                    964 *                                                                       C1R09760
                                    965 *********************************************************************** C1R09770
 
 
 
                                    967 *********************************************************************** C1R09790
                                    968 * READ 2311 RELOCATABLE DIRECTORY (RLD) AND SET UP TO CREATE 2314       C1R09800
                                    969 *      DIRECTORY.                                                       C1R09810
                                    970 *                                                                       C1R09820
                                    971 *   RLD STARTS AT THE ADDRESS POINTED TO BY C0H1R2 ON 2311.  THE        C1R09830
                                    972 *   ADDRESS WAS SAVED DURING DURING THE TRANSFER OF C0H1 FROM 2311      C1R09840
                                    973 *   TO 2314.                                                            C1R09850
                                    974 *                                                                       C1R09860
                                    975 *   THE NEW RLD IS LOCATED AT THE 2314 C0H1R2, BUT WE CAN JUST USE      C1R09870
                                    976 *   THE RELOCATABLE LIBRARY STATUS RECORD TO LOCATE THINGS.             C1R09880
                                    977 *                                                                       C1R09890
                                    978 *   AS DIRECTORY RECORDS ARE COPIED, THE ENTRIES ARE ALTERED TO         C1R09900
                                    979 *   UPDATE THE CHR USING 2314 TRACK GEOMETRY.  THE 2311 CHR IS          C1R09910
                                    980 *   CONVERTED TO A BLOCK ADDRESS RELATIVE TO THE START OF THE 2311      C1R09920
                                    981 *   LIBRARY AND THEN CONVERTED BACK TO A 2314 CCHHRR.                   C1R09930
                                    982 *                                                                       C1R09940
                                    983 *   REGISTER USAGE:                                                     C1R09950
                                    984 *      R6 - COUNT OF 2314 DIR ENTRIES LEFT IN CURRENT DIR RECORD        C1R09960
                                    985 *      R7 - POINTER TO CURRENT 2314 DIRECTORY RECORD                    C1R09970
                                    986 *      R8 - COUNT OF 2311 DIR ENTRIES LEFT IN CURRENT DIR RECORD        C1R09980
                                    987 *      R9 - POINTER TO CURRENT 2311 DIRECTORY RECORD                    C1R09990
                                    988 *                                                                       C1R10000

       CONVERT 2311 SYSRES TO 2314   COPY RELOCATABLE LIB                                                      PAGE   27
 
 
  LOC  OBJECT CODE    ADDR1 ADDR2  STMT   SOURCE STATEMENT                                          DOS CL3-10 03/29/70.

                                   1014 *                                                                       C1R10260

                                   1267 *********************************************************************** C1R12790
                                   1268 *                                                                       C1R12800
                                   1269 * THE SOURCE 2311 SYSRES USED FOR THIS PROGRAM INCLUDES A CORE IMAGE    C1R12810
                                   1270 * LIBRARY AND A RELOCATABLE LIBRARY (ALREADY COPIED).  A SECOND SYSRES  C1R12820
                                   1271 * INCLUDES A SOURCE STATEMENT LIBRARY THAT MUST BE COPIED TO THE        C1R12830
                                   1272 * TARGET 2314 SYSRES.                                                   C1R12840
                                   1273 *                                                                       C1R12850
                                   1274 * COPY THE SOURCE STATEMENT LIBRARY.  THIS IS MUCH THE SAME AS THE      C1R12860
                                   1275 * RELOCATABLE LIBRARY, AND AS WITH THE RELOCATABLE LIBRARY, THE         C1R12870
                                   1276 * DIRECTORY AND LIBRARY BLOCK SIZES ARE THE SAME ON 2311 AND 2314.      C1R12880
                                   1277 *                                                                       C1R12890
                                   1278 * AND THE DIRECTORY IS A TEENY BIT MORE DIFFICULT BECAUSE THE FIRST 80  C1R12900
                                   1279 * BYTES OF THE FIRST DIRECTORY RECORD (EQUAL TO FIVE ENTRIES) IS USED   C1R12910
                                   1280 * FOR THE DIRECTORY CONTROL RECORD.                                     C1R12920
                                   1281 *                                                                       C1R12930
                                   1282 * BECAUSE BLOCK SIZES ARE THE SAME FOR DIR AND LIBRARY, WE'LL JUST      C1R12940
                                   1283 * COPY THE DIRECTORY AND THE LIBRARY BLOCK FOR BLOCK FROM THE 2311      C1R12950
                                   1284 * VOLUME TO THE 2314 VOLUME.  WHILE PROCESSING THE DIRECTORY, WE'LL     C1R12960
                                   1285 * RECALCULATE THE BBCCHHR FROM 2311 TO 2314 BY CONVERTING IT TO A       C1R12970
                                   1286 * RELATIVE BLOCK ADDRESS FROM THE START OF THE LIBRARY AND THEN         C1R12980
                                   1287 * CONVERTING THAT BACK TO THE CORRECT BBCCHHR TO 2314 TRACK GEOMETRY    C1R12990
                                   1288 *                                                                       C1R13000
                                   1289 * THIS SOURCE STATEMENT LIBRARY COMES FROM ANOTHER SYSRES VOLUME,       C1R13010
                                   1290 * NOT THE SAME ONE THAT THE RELO AND CORE IMAGE LIBRARIES CAME FROM,    C1R13020
                                   1291 * BUT IT IS PART OF THE SAME DISTRIBUTION TAPE.                         C1R13030
                                   1292 *                                                                       C1R13040
                                   1293 *********************************************************************** C1R13050
 
 
 
                                   1295 *********************************************************************** C1R13070
                                   1296 * READ 2311 SOURCE STATEMENT DIRECTORY (SLD) AND SET UP TO CREATE 2314  C1R13080
                                   1297 *      DIRECTORY.                                                       C1R13090
                                   1298 *                                                                       C1R13100
                                   1299 *   SLD STARTS AT THE ADDRESS POINTED TO BY C0H1R3 ON SLB2311.  THE     C1R13110
                                   1300 *   ADDRESS WAS SAVED DURING INITIALIZATION OF THIS PROGRAM             C1R13120
                                   1301 *                                                                       C1R13130
                                   1302 *   THE NEW SLD IS POINTED TO BY 2314 C0H1R2, BUT WE CAN JUST USE       C1R13140
                                   1303 *   THE SOURCE STATEMENT LIBRARY STATUS RECORD TO LOCATE THINGS.        C1R13150
                                   1304 *                                                                       C1R13160
                                   1305 *   AS DIRECTORY ENTRIES ARE COPIED, THEY ARE ALTERED TO UPDATE THE     C1R13170
                                   1306 *   CHR USING 2314 TRACK GEOMETRY.  THE 2311 CHR IS CONVERTED TO A      C1R13180
                                   1307 *   BLOCK ADDRESS RELATIVE TO THE START OF THE 2311 LIBRARY AND THEN    C1R13190
                                   1308 *   CONVERTED BACK TO A 2314 CCHHRR.                                    C1R13200
                                   1309 *                                                                       C1R13210
                                   1310 *   REGISTER USAGE:                                                     C1R13220
                                   1311 *      R6 - COUNT OF 2314 DIR ENTRIES LEFT IN CURRENT DIR RECORD        C1R13230
                                   1312 *      R7 - POINTER TO CURRENT 2314 DIRECTORY RECORD                    C1R13240
                                   1313 *      R8 - COUNT OF 2311 DIR ENTRIES LEFT IN CURRENT DIR RECORD        C1R13250
                                   1314 *      R9 - POINTER TO CURRENT 2311 DIRECTORY RECORD                    C1R13260
                                   1315 *                                                                       C1R13270

                                   1738 *********************************************************************** C1R17390
                                   1739 *                                                                       C1R17400
                                   1740 * INITIALIZE AN AREA OF STORAGE.  THE FIRST BYTE OF THE AREA HAS BEEN   C1R17410
                                   1741 * SET BY THE CALLER TO THE VALUE TO BE USED TO CLEAR THE REST OF THE    C1R17420
                                   1742 * AREA.                                                                 C1R17430
                                   1743 *                                                                       C1R17440
                                   1744 * AT ENTRY:                                                             C1R17450
                                   1745 *    R0 CONTAINS THE LENGTH OF THE AREA TO BE INITIALIZED, INCLUDING    C1R17460
                                   1746 *       THE FIRST BYTE OF THE AREA, WHICH HAS BEEN SET BY THE CALLER    C1R17470
                                   1747 *       TO THE VALUE TO BE PROPAGATED THROUGH THE REST OF THE AREA.     C1R17480
                                   1748 *    R1 POINTS AT THE FIRST BYTE OF THE AREA TO BE INITIALIZED, WHICH   C1R17490
                                   1749 *       HAS BEEN SET BY THE CALLER TO THE INITIALIZATION VALUE.         C1R17500
                                   1750 *    R2 CALLER'S RETURN ADDRESS                                         C1R17510
                                   1751 *    FIRST BYTE OF AREA HAS BEEN SET BY THE CALLER TO THE VALUE         C1R17520
                                   1752 *    TO WHICH THE AREA SHOULD BE INITIALIZED.                           C1R17530
                                   1753 *                                                                       C1R17540
                                   1754 * EXAMPLE - TO INITIALIZE THE DIR4 CORE IMAGE DIRECTORY RECORD TO       C1R17550
                                   1755 *           BLANKS                                                      C1R17560
                                   1756 *    R0 SET TO 360, THE LENGTH OF A CORE IMAGE DIRECTORY RECORD         C1R17570
                                   1757 *    R1 SET TO THE ADDRESS OF DIR4                                      C1R17580
                                   1758 *    DIR4 BYTE ONE SET TO C' '                                          C1R17590
                                   1759 *                                                                       C1R17600
                                   1760 * REGISTER USAGE:                                                       C1R17610
                                   1761 *    R0  - AREA LENGTH, NOT SAVED BY THIS ROUTINE                       C1R17620
                                   1762 *    R1  - AREA POINTER, ALSO NOT SAVED BY THIS ROUTINE                 C1R17630
                                   1763 *    R2  - CALLER'S RETURN ADDRESS                                      C1R17640
                                   1764 *    R14 - WORK REGISTER, NOT SAVED NOR RESTORED                        C1R17650
                                   1765 *                                                                       C1R17660
                                   1766 *********************************************************************** C1R17670

002154 0602                        1770          BCTR  R0,R2               DECREMENT (INITIAL BYTE ALREADY SET) C1R17710
                                   1771 *                                  ..AND RETURN IF INIT'ING 1-BYTE AREA C1R17720

                                   1773 *                                  LENGTH OF LAST SEG IN R1 HIGH BYTE   C1R17740
00215A 1200                        1774          LTR   R0,R0               ANY 256-BYTE SEGMENTS                C1R17750
00215C 47D0 B96E            0216E  1775          BNP   INITLAST            ..NO, JUST DO LAST SEGMENT           C1R17760
                                   1776 *                                                                       C1R17770

       CONVERT 2311 SYSRES TO 2314    XIO/XOIFW SUBROUTINE                                                     PAGE   45

                                   1800 *********************************************************************** C1R18010
                                   1801 *                                                                       C1R18020
                                   1802 * EXECUTE 2314 CHANNEL PROGRAM AND WAIT FOR COMPLETION.  NO ERROR       C1R18030
                                   1803 * HANDLING AS THIS PROGRAM RUNS IN AN EMULATION ENVIRONMENT.            C1R18040
                                   1804 *                                                                       C1R18050
                                   1805 * ENTRY POINTS                                                          C1R18060
                                   1806 *    XIO - USED FOR READS AND DATA-ONLY (NON-FORMATTING WRITES)         C1R18070
                                   1807 *    XIOFW - USED FOR FORMATTING WRITES OF A SINGLE RECORD.  THIS       C1R18080
                                   1808 *       ROUTINE WILL CONSTRUCT A COUNT FIELD AT THE START OF THE I/O    C1R18090
                                   1809 *       AREA FROM CCW INFORMATION AND THE SEARCH FIELD POINTED TO       C1R18100
                                   1810 *       BY R1.  COUNT FIELD KEYLEN ALWAYS SET TO ZERO FOR THIS.         C1R18110
                                   1811 *                                                                       C1R18120
                                   1812 * AT ENTRY:                                                             C1R18130
                                   1813 *    R1 POINTS AT THE OPERATION'S CURSOR, WHICH INCLUDES THE            C1R18140
                                   1814 *         SEEK/SEARCH BBCCHHR ID AND THE ADDRESS OF THE DTFPH TO BE     C1R18150
                                   1815 *         USED                                                          C1R18160
                                   1816 *    R15 POINTS AT THE CALLER'S CCW(S).  THESE CCWS LOGICALLY FOLLOW    C1R18170
                                   1817 *        THE SEEK/SEARCH/TIC NEEDED TO LOCATE CYL/HEAD/REC FOR THE      C1R18180
                                   1818 *        OPERATION REQUESTED BY THE CALLER                              C1R18190
                                   1819 *    DATA AREA POINTED TO BY ANY/ALL CCWS SET AS NEEDED                 C1R18200
                                   1820 *                                                                       C1R18210
                                   1821 * NOTE:                                                                 C1R18220
                                   1822 *    FOR FORMATTING WRITE OPERATIONS WHEN WRITING MULTIPLE RECORDS      C1R18230
                                   1823 *    (COMMAND-CHAINING FORMATTING WRITE CCW'S), CALLER IS EXPECTED      C1R18240
                                   1824 *    TO PROVIDE COUNT FIELDS AND SHOULD USE THE XIO ENTRY POINT.        C1R18250
                                   1825 *                                                                       C1R18260
                                   1826 * REGISTER USAGE:                                                       C1R18270
                                   1827 *    R0  = WORK REGISTER, NOT SAVED NOR RESTORED (XIOFW ENTRY ONLY)     C1R18280
                                   1828 *    R1  = POINTER TO BBCCHHR FOR READ/WRITE/REWRITE OPERATION          C1R18290
                                   1829 *    R2  = CALLER RETURN ADDRESS                                        C1R18300
                                   1830 *    R14 = WORK REGISTER, NOT SAVED NOR RESTORED (XIOFW ENTRY ONLY)     C1R18310
                                   1831 *    R15 = POINTER TO CALLER'S CCW(S).  AFTER EXCP POINTS TO CCB/DTFPH  C1R18320
                                   1832 *                                                                       C1R18330
                                   1833 *********************************************************************** C1R18340
 
000000                             1835          USING CRSRAD,R1                                                C1R18360

                                   1869 *********************************************************************** C1R18640
                                   1870 *                                                                       C1R18650
                                   1871 * INCREMENT SEEK/SEARCH BBCCHHR TO NEXT RECORD, ADJUSTING FOR END OF    C1R18660
                                   1872 * TRACK AND END OF CYLINDER.  NUMBER OF RECORDS PER TRACK AND TRACKS    C1R18670
                                   1873 * PER CYLINDER ARE PROVIDED BY THE CALLER IN THE PARAMETER DATA         C1R18680
                                   1874 * STRUCTURE POINTED TO BY R1.                                           C1R18690
                                   1875 *                                                                       C1R18700
                                   1876 * NOTE THAT SEEK/SEARCH BBCCHHR FOR WRITE COUNT-KEY-DATA IS FOR THE     C1R18710
                                   1877 * RECORD *PRIOR* TO THE ONE BEING WRITTEN, WHILE FOR READ OR WRITE      C1R18720
                                   1878 * JUST DATA (NON-FORMATTING I/O), THE BBCCHHR IS FOR THE RECORD         C1R18730
                                   1879 * BEING READ OR WRITTEN.  THIS AFFECTS END-OF-TRACK LOGIC               C1R18740
                                   1880 *                                                                       C1R18750
                                   1881 * AT ENTRY:                                                             C1R18760
                                   1882 *    R1 POINTS TO DATA STRUCTURE NXTCHRAD.  SEE DSECT NXTCHRAD FOR      C1R18770
                                   1883 *    LAYOUT AND CONTENTS.  THE CURRENT BBCCHHR IS AT THE BEGINNING      C1R18780
                                   1884 *    OF THIS STRUCTURE AND IS UPDATED BY THIS ROUTINE.                  C1R18790
                                   1885 *                                                                       C1R18800
                                   1886 * AT EXIT:                                                              C1R18810
                                   1887 *    BBCCHHR POINTED TO BY R1 UPDATED TO NEXT RECORD, WITH TRACK        C1R18820
                                   1888 *       AND CYL ADJUSTED AS NEEDED.                                     C1R18830
                                   1889 *    RETURN CODE IN R15                                                 C1R18840
                                   1890 *         ZERO - END OF EXTENT HAS NOT BEEN REACHED                     C1R18850
                                   1891 *         4    - NEXT RECORD TO BE WRITTEN EXCEEDS THE EXTENT           C1R18860
                                   1892 *                                                                       C1R18870
                                   1893 * REGISTER USAGE:                                                       C1R18880
                                   1894 *    R0 = WORK REGISTER USED NOT SAVED OR RESTORED BY THIS ROUTINE      C1R18890
                                   1895 *    R1 = SET BY CALLER                                                 C1R18900
                                   1896 *    R2 = CALLER RETURN ADDRESS                                         C1R18910
                                   1897 *    R14 = WORK REGISTER USED NOT SAVED OR RESTORED BY THIS ROUTINE     C1R18920
                                   1898 *    R15 = RETURN CODE REGISTER.  ALSO USED AS WORK REGISTER.           C1R18930
                                   1899 *                                                                       C1R18940
                                   1900 *********************************************************************** C1R18950

                                   1947 *********************************************************************** C1R19420
                                   1948 *                                                                       C1R19430
                                   1949 * TRANSLATE A 2311 BBCCHHR TO THE EQUIVALENT LOCATION ON A 2314.        C1R19440
                                   1950 *                                                                       C1R19450
                                   1951 * THIS ROUTINE DOES A TWO-STEP TRANSLATION.  FIRST, THE 2311 BBCCHHR    C1R19460
                                   1952 * IS CONVERTED TO A BLOCK NUMBER RELATIVE TO THE START OF THE LIBRARY   C1R19470
                                   1953 * OR DIRECTORY THAT CONTAINS THE BBCCHHR.  SECOND, THE ROUTINE          C1R19480
                                   1954 * CONVERTS THE BLOCK NUMBER BACK TO AN ABSOLUTE BBCCHHR ON A 2314.      C1R19490
                                   1955 *                                                                       C1R19500
                                   1956 * THE INPUT CURSOR PROVIDES THE DEVICE TRACK GEOMETRY, RECORDS PER      C1R19510
                                   1957 * TRACK, AND DIRECTORY OR LIBRARY ABSOLUTE STARTING TRACK FOR THE       C1R19520
                                   1958 * INPUT BBCCHHR.  THE OUTPUT CURSOR PROVIDES THE SAME INFORMATION FOR   C1R19530
                                   1959 * THE TARGET 2314 LIBRARY OR DIRECTORY.  USE OF CURSOR DATA ELIMINATES  C1R19540
                                   1960 * ANY NEED FOR THIS ROUTINE TO KNOW WHAT KIND OF LIBRARY OR DIRECTORY   C1R19550
                                   1961 * IS BEING PROCESSED.                                                   C1R19560
                                   1962 *                                                                       C1R19570
                                   1963 * AT ENTRY:                                                             C1R19580
                                   1964 *    FIELD WORKBCHR CONTAINS THE INPUT BBCCHHR                          C1R19590
                                   1965 *    R0 POINTS TO THE OUTPUT CURSOR                                     C1R19600
                                   1966 *    R1 POINTS TO THE INPUT CURSOR                                      C1R19610
                                   1967 *    R2 CALLER'S RETURN ADDRESS                                         C1R19620
                                   1968 *                                                                       C1R19630
                                   1969 * AT EXIT:                                                              C1R19640
                                   1970 *    FIELD WORKBCHR CONTAINS THE OUTPUT BBCCHHR                         C1R19650
                                   1971 *    R0 POINTS TO THE OUTPUT CURSOR                                     C1R19660
                                   1972 *    R1 POINTS TO THE OUTPUT CURSOR (NOTE CHANGE IN R1 CONTENTS)        C1R19670
                                   1973 *    R2 CALLER'S RETURN ADDRESS                                         C1R19680
                                   1974 *                                                                       C1R19690
                                   1975 * REGISTER USAGE:                                                       C1R19700
                                   1976 *    R0 = POINTER TO OUTPUT CURSOR                                      C1R19710
                                   1977 *    R1 = POINTER TO INPUT CURSOR, THEN TO OUTPUT CURSOR                C1R19720
                                   1978 *    R2 = CALLER RETURN ADDRESS                                         C1R19730
                                   1979 *    R14 = WORK REGISTER USED NOT SAVED OR RESTORED BY THIS ROUTINE     C1R19740
                                   1980 *    R15 = WORK REGISTER USED NOT SAVED OR RESTORED BY THIS ROUTINE     C1R19750
                                   1981 *                                                                       C1R19760
                                   1982 *********************************************************************** C1R19770
 
 
 
002226                             1984 XLATBCHR DS    0H                  TRANSLATE A DISK ADDR 2311 TO 2314   C1R19790

                                   2132 *********************************************************************** C1R20810
                                   2133 *                                                                       C1R20820
                                   2134 * CONSTANTS IN THE THREE STATUS RECORDS BELOW REFLECT THE FIXED         C1R20830
                                   2135 * ALLOCATION FOR THE SYSRES BUILT BY THIS PROGRAM, WHICH ARE SET IN     C1R20840
                                   2136 * EQUATE STATEMENTS AT THE BEGINNING OF THE PROGRAM.                    C1R20850
                                   2137 *                                                                       C1R20860
                                   2138 * IN ADDITION TO BEING THE REFERENCE FOR THE RESPECTIVE LIBRARY         C1R20870
                                   2139 * ALLOCATIONS, THESE RECORDS ARE UPDATED AS PHASES, RELOCATABLE         C1R20880
                                   2140 * MODULES, AND SOURCE BOOKS ARE WRITTEN TO THE NEW SYSRES. AS EACH      C1R20890
                                   2141 * LIBRARY IS COPIED, THE APPROPRIATE LIBRARY STATUS RECORD IS UPDATED   C1R20900
                                   2142 * ON THE NEW SYSRES.                                                    C1R20910

                                   2629 *********************************************************************** C1R25780
                                   2630 *                                                                       C1R25790
                                   2631 *  DTFPH MACROS ARE REQUIRED TO CREATE DASD FORMAT-1 LABELS AND         C1R25800
                                   2632 *  ENABLE ACCESS IF DASD FILE PROTECTION IS ENABLED.                    C1R25810
                                   2633 *                                                                       C1R25820
                                   2634 *  THE FIRST BYTES OF DTFPH ARE THE CCB FOR I/O OPERATIONS.  BECAUSE    C1R25830
                                   2635 *  ALL I/O OPERATIONS ARE SYNCHRONOUS, WE CAN POINT ALL DTFPH AT THE    C1R25840
                                   2636 *  SAME LEAD-IN CCW STRING.                                             C1R25850
                                   2637 *                                                                       C1R25860
                                   2638 *  THE LEAD-IN CCW STRING INCLUDES SEEK, SEARCH, TIC *-8, FOLLOWED BY   C1R25870
                                   2639 *  A TIC TO THE CCW OR STRING THAT THE REQUESTOR WANTS EXECUTED.  THIS  C1R25880
                                   2640 *  MEANS THAT ONE SEEK/SEARCH AREA IS USED.                             C1R25890
                                   2641 *                                                                       C1R25900
                                   2642 *********************************************************************** C1R25910

                                   2647 * TO THE CALLER-REQUESTED CCW OR CCW STRING.  BECAUSE ALL I/O IN THIS   C1R25960

       DOS SUPERVISOR - INTERRUPT HANDLER ROUTINES                                                             PAGE   17

                                    574+*  THE OBJECTIVE OF THE SUPERVISOR INTERRUPT HANDLER ROUTINE
                                    575+*  IS TO BRANCH TO THE CORRECT SVC ROUTINE
000000                              576+         USING SVEARA,R9
000670                              577+ENTSVC   EQU   * 3-2
000670 909F 0320            00320   578+         STM   R9,RF,ERA SAVE ENTRY REGS              3-9
                                    579+*                                                                   3-1
                                    580+*              THIS HOOK DEPENDS ON REG 9,10,11 BEING STORED AT ERA 3-1
                                    581+*              AND THOSE REG BEING AVAILABLE FOR USE.  ALSO THE VALU3-1
                                    582+*              OF THE PIK MUST BE CORRECT AT THIS TIME.             3-1
                                    583+*              THE FOLLOWING SIX STATEMENTS ARE USED BY THE CE      3-1
                                    584+*                            FETCH-LOAD ROUTINE                     3-1
                                    585+*                                                                   3-1
000674 47F0 06D4            006D4   586+CEFLTHK1 BC    15,NOCEFLT1 BRANCH UNLESS FETCH/LOAD TRACE ACTIVE  3-1
000678 9107 0023      00023         587+         TM    35(0),X'07' TEST FOR A SUPERVISOR CALL 0 OR 7      3-1
00067C 47B0 06D4            006D4   588+         BC    NM,NOCEFLT1 YES, BRANCH                            3-1
000680 4190 0008            00008   589+         LA    R9,L'CEFLTAB GET LOOP COUNT                   3-11
000684 41A0 06BE            006BE   590+         LA    RA,CEFLTAB+L'CEFLTAB INITIALYZE POINTER             3-11
000688                              591+CEFLTLP  EQU   * 3-11
000688 D500 0023 A000 00023 00000   592+         CLC   SVOLDP+3(1),0(RA) DOES CODE MATCH                  3-11
00068E 4780 069E            0069E   593+         BE    CEFLIDRA YES, TEST IF IDRA BUSY           3-11
000692 41AA 0001            00001   594+         LA    RA,1(RA) UPDATE POINTER TO SVC TO TEST    3-11
000696 4690 0688            00688   595+         BCT   R9,CEFLTLP NO,LOOP UNTIL ALL TESTED         3-11
00069A 47F0 06BE            006BE   596+         B     CEFLIDNO NO MATCH,CONTINUE NORMAL         3-11
00069E                              597+CEFLIDRA EQU   * 3-11
00069E 9500 009B      0009B         598+         CLI   TRTIDRA,IDRA00 IS IDRA BUSY                     3-11
0006A2 4770 06BE            006BE   599+         BNE   CEFLIDNO NO,CONTINUE NORMAL               3-11
0006A6 9220 0291      00291         600+         MVI   HLDPSW,X'20' INDICATE SVCINTERRUPT            3-11
0006AA 4590 04E0            004E0   601+         BAL   R9,GENENT INITIALYZE ENTRY                 3-11
0006AE 4190 025A            0025A   602+         LA    R9,EXT01 SET UP EXIT                      3-11
0006B2 47F0 C1C8            021C8   603+         B     RESVC RE-ISSUE SVC UNTIL IDRA FREE     3-11
0006B6 0102030405060B0E             604+CEFLTAB  DC    X'0102030405060B0E' SVC CODES FOR FLTRACE           3-11
0006BE                              605+CEFLIDNO DS    0H CONTINUE HERE IF NO PROBLEM      3-11

0006C2 D201 0090 048E 00090 0048E   607+         MVC   CEPIK(2),PIK 3-4

0006DC 4190 025A            0025A   614+         LA    R9,EXT01

                                   1901+*360N-CL-453 SGTCON    CHANGE LEBEL 3-12                           3-12
                                   1902+*   THE OBJECTIVE OF VLDADR1,VLDADR2,AND VLDADR3 IS TO VALIDATE THE
                                   1903+*   UPPER AND LOWER LIMITS OF A FIELD. THESE LIMITS MUST BE WITHIN  3-7
                                   1904+*   CORE. FOR USER ROUTINES,THE LOWER LIMIT MUST NOT BE INSIDE THE
                                   1905+*   SUPERVISOR. ALSO BOTH LIMITS MUST HAVE USER'S KEY.
0016A0 4860 048E            0048E  1906+VLDADR1  LH    R6,PIK LD KEY
0016A4 4122 0000            00000  1907+VLDADR3  LA    R2,0(R2) CLEAR HI BYTE
0016A8 5920 0420            00420  1908+VLDADR2  C     R2,EOCADR IS HIGH ADDR GR THAN HIGH CORE
0016AC 4720 00DE            000DE  1909+         BH    ERR25 YES,CANCEL
0016B0 1266                        1910+         LTR   R6,R6 NO,DOES USER KEY EQUAL ZERO
0016B2 0787                        1911+         BCR   E,R7 YES,RETURN
0016B4 4111 0000            00000  1912+         LA    R1,0(R1) CLEAR HI BYTE
0016B8 5910 0420            00420  1913+         C     R1,EOCADR LOW ADDR GR THEN HIGH CORE             3-7
0016BC 4720 00DE            000DE  1914+         BH    ERR25 YES,CANCEL                             3-7
0016C0 4910 B746            01746  1915+         CH    R1,ENDSUP NO,IS LOWER LIMIT IN SUPERVISOR
0016C4 4740 00DE            000DE  1916+         BL    ERR25 YES,CANCEL
0016C8 1B88                        1917+         SR    R8,R8 NO, CLEAR COMPARE REG
0016CA 1851                        1918+         LR    R5,R1
0016CC 4350 D64E            0364E  1919+         IC    R5,CLRCOM+2 CLEAR LOW ORDER BYTE OF ADDR
0016D0 0985                        1920+         ISK   R8,R5
0016D2 4850 041E            0041E  1921+         LH    R5,PID GET STORAGE PROTECT KEY      3-3
0016D6 1958                        1922+         CR    R5,R8 IS REQUESTOR KEY CORRECT     3-3
0016D8 4770 00DE            000DE  1923+         BNE   ERR25 NO
0016DC 1852                        1924+         LR    R5,R2
0016DE 4350 D64E            0364E  1925+         IC    R5,CLRCOM+2 CLEAR LAST BYTE OF ADDRESS
0016E2 0985                        1926+         ISK   R8,R5 INSERT KEY
0016E4 4850 041E            0041E  1927+         LH    R5,PID GET STORAGE PROTECT KEY      3-3
0016E8 1958                        1928+         CR    R5,R8 IS REQUESTOR KEY CORRECT     3-3
0016EA 4770 00DE            000DE  1929+         BNE   ERR25 NO,CANCEL
0016EE 07F7                        1930+         BR    R7 RETURN TO CALLER

                                   3755+* MOVE TID OF SUBTASK BEING ATTACHED INTO MVCFLD TO GIVE IT CORRECT*
                                   3756+* PRIORITY DURING TASK SELECTION. THIS WILL BE ACCOMPLISHED BY     *
                                   3757+* MOVING ONE BYTE AT A TIME,FROM LEFT TO RIGHT, ONE BYTE STARTING  *
                                   3758+* AT THE RIGHT END OF MVCFLD. WHEN THE ATTACHING TASK IS REACHED,  *
                                   3759+* THE TID WILL BE PLACED IN THE NEXT BYTE TO THE LEFT OF IT.       *

                                   3948+********************************************************************
                                   3949+* THIS SUBROUTINE INSERTS THE ABSOLUTE PRIORITY OF ALL ACTIVE TASKS*
                                   3950+* IN THE EXTENSION TO THEIR PIB TABLE ENTRIES.

002FAE 1B33                        3955+         SR    R3,R3 CLEAR INDEX REGISTER

002FB8 0787                        3959+         BCR   E,R7 IF SO-EXIT

                                   4004+********************************************************************
                                   4005+********************************************************************
                                   4006+* THIS SUBROUTINE REMOVES ANY TASK THAT IS WAITING FOR THE ECB     *
                                   4007+* WHOSE ADDRESS IS IN R1 TO BE POSTED FROM THE WAIT STATE          *
                                   4008+********************************************************************
                                   4009+********************************************************************
003032                             4010+UNWAIT   EQU   * REMOVE WAITING TASKS SUBROUTINE
003032 4160 BA22            01A22  4011+         LA    R6,MVCFLD+2 POINT TO 40 IN MVCFLD
003036 4840 044A            0044A  4012+         LH    R4,PIBPT POINT TO PIB TABLE
00303A                             4013+UNW001   EQU   *
00303A 4166 0001            00001  4014+         LA    R6,1(R6) BUMP TO NEXT MVCFLD BYTE
00303E 9500 6000      00000        4015+         CLI   0(R6),X'00' END OF MVCFLD
003042 0787                        4016+         BCR   E,R7 IF SO-EXIT
003044 1B55                        4017+         SR    R5,R5 CLEAR INDEX REGISTER
003046 4356 0000            00000  4018+         IC    R5,0(R6) GET PIB DISPLACEMENT
00304A 1A54                        4019+         AR    R5,R4 POINT TO PIB ENTRY
00304C 9580 5000      00000        4020+         CLI   0(R5),X'80' IS THIS TASK ACTIVE
003050 4780 D03A            0303A  4021+         BE    UNW001 IF NOT-GO TO NEXT PIB

                                   4053+********************************************************************
                                   4054+* ENQ MACRO ROUTINE                                                *
                                   4055+********************************************************************

                                   4057+* VALIDATE THE ADDRESS OF THE RCB                                  *
0030C6                             4058+SVC42    EQU   *
0030C6 1810                        4059+         LR    R1,R0 LOAD LO LIMIT REG
0030C8 4121 0007            00007  4060+         LA    R2,7(R1) LOAD HI LIMIT REG
0030CC 4570 B6A0            016A0  4061+         BAL   R7,VLDADR1 VALIDATE THE ADDRESS OF RCB
0030D0 1B44                        4062+         SR    R4,R4 CLEAR ECB ADDRESS REGISTER
0030D2 4830 046C            0046C  4063+         LH    R3,PIB2PTR POINT TO 2ND HALF PIB TABLE
0030D6 4A30 048E            0048E  4064+         AH    R3,PIK POINT TO CORRECT ENTRY
0030DA 9540 048F      0048F        4065+         CLI   PIK+1,X'40' IS THIS A MAIN TASK
0030DE 4740 D0EC            030EC  4066+         BL    SVC42A IF SO-NO ECB REQUIRED

                                   4068+* A SUBTASK MUST HAVE AN ECB TO ENQ                                *
0030E2 5843 0008            00008  4069+         L     R4,8(R3) PICKUP ECB ADDRESS
0030E6 1244                        4070+         LTR   R4,R4 DOES IT HAVE AN ECB ADDRESS
0030E8 4780 00D6            000D6  4071+         BZ    ERR21 IF NOT-ILLEGAL SVC

                                   4073+* TEST TO SEE IF RESOURCE IS AVAILABLE                             *
0030EC                             4074+SVC42A   EQU   *
0030EC 9300 1000      00000        4075+         TS    0(R1) IS THE RESOURCE AVAILABLE
0030F0 4770 D0FC            030FC  4076+         BNZ   SVC42B IF NOT-GO DETERMINE OWNER
0030F4 5041 0004            00004  4077+         ST    R4,4(R1) PUT ECB ADR IN RCB AS OWNER ID
0030F8 47F0 025A            0025A  4078+         B     EXT01 GO TO INTERRUPTED TASK

                                   4080+* THE RESOURCE WAS UNAVAILABLE                                     *
0030FC                             4081+SVC42B   EQU   *
0030FC 5821 0004            00004  4082+         L     R2,4(R1) GET OWNER ECBADR FROM ECB
003100 4122 0000            00000  4083+         LA    R2,0(R2) WIPE OUT HI BYTE
003104 1222                        4084+         LTR   R2,R2 TEST FOR MAINTASK OWNERSHIP           3-10
003106 4780 D112            03112  4085+         BZ    SVC42C BRANCH IF YES                        3-10
00310A 9180 2002      00002        4086+         TM    2(R2),X'80' HAS OWNER TERMINATED
00310E 4710 00D6            000D6  4087+         BO    ERR21 IF SO ILLEGAL SVC
003112 1924                        4088+SVC42C   CR    R2,R4 IS OWNER ENQUING                      3-10
003114 4780 00D6            000D6  4089+         BE    ERR21 IF SO-ILLEGAL NESTED ENQ
003118 9680 1004      00004        4090+         OI    4(R1),X'80' SET RESOURCE-WANTED BIT IN RCB
00311C 5A30 0484            00484  4091+         A     R3,PIBDIFF POINT TO ENTRY IN PIB TABLE
003120 94FE 3000      00000        4092+         NI    0(R3),X'FE' PUT ENQING TASK IN WAIT STATE
003124 5843 0004            00004  4093+         L     R4,4(R3) GET TASKS SAVE ADDRESS
003128 5024 0030            00030  4094+         ST    R2,48(R4) OWNER ECBADR TO ENQ TSKS R1
00312C 47F0 C1C8            021C8  4095+         B     RESVC SETUP TO REDRIVE THE ENQ SVC

                                   4283+* PASS AB SAVE ADDR TO USER IN HIS R1

                                   5889+*        THIS TEMPORARY CODE IN THE LTA IS USED TO MODIFY THE 5 BYTE
                                   5890+*        CONSTANT IN PUBSAVE WITH REGARD TO SYSRES BEING ON THE SELEC-
                                   5891+*        TOR CHANNEL OR NOT, AND ALSO TO INITIALIZE RECORD LENGTH FOR
                                   5892+*        THE CIL DEPENDENT ON WHETHER SYSRES IS A 2311 OR A 2314.
                                   5893+*
                                   5894+*        ENTRY IS FROM THE FETCH-ROUTINE THE FIRST TIME IT IS EXECUTED,
                                   5895+*        WHEREAFTER THIS ROUTINE TERMINATES BY REPLACING THE TEMPORARY
                                   5896+*        LINKAGE INSTRUCTIONS IN FETCH WITH THE FINAL ONES AND THEN
                                   5897+*        EXITS TO THE REPLACED CODE IN FETCH.


005568                             5899+         ORG   LTA
005568                             5900+         USING *,RF ESTABL. ADDRESSIBILITY IN LTA
005568 4880 D648            03648  5901+         LH    R8,PUBRES GET SYSRES PUB ADDR
000000                             5902+         USING PUBADR,R8
