// JOB SYSGEN03  ZAPRELO ASSEMBLE AND CATALOG                           00.12.34
// OPTION CATAL
 PHASE ZAPRELO,S
// EXEC ASSEMBLY
 

ZAPR                                          EXTERNAL SYMBOL DICTIONARY                                       PAGE    1


SYMBOL   TYPE ID  ADDR  LENGTH LD ID

ZAPRELO   SD  01 000000 000350
IJGFIZZZ  ER  02
IJGFOZZZ  ER  03

ZAPR   APPLY REP CARDS TO RELOCATABLE MODULE                                                                   PAGE    1


  LOC  OBJECT CODE    ADDR1 ADDR2  STMT   SOURCE STATEMENT                                          FDOS CL3-10 03/31/70

                                      2 ***********************************************************************
                                      3 *
                                      4 * COPY A SINGLE RELOCATABLE MODULE FROM A CARD IMAGE SYSPCH FILE,
                                      5 * ADDING REP CARDS JUST PRIOR TO THE END CARD.
                                      6 *
                                      7 * IN REAL LIFE, DOS SYSTEMS HAD A CARD READER AND A PUNCH.  SO
                                      8 * PUNCHING OUT THE RELOCATABLE MODULE, HAND-KEYING THE REP CARDS,
                                      9 * ADDING THEM TO THE OBJECT DECK AT THE RIGHT POINT, AND CATALOGING
                                     10 * THE UPDATED DECK WAS A TRIVIAL EXERCISE.
                                     11 *
                                     12 * IF DOS HAD INCLUDED AN OBJMAINT UTILITY, THIS PROGRAM WOULD NOT
                                     13 * BE NEEDED.  BUT DOS WAS NEVER DESIGNED FOR CARDLESS OPERATION.
                                     14 *
                                     15 * INPUT
                                     16 *   UIN, SYS004, UNBLOCKED CARD-IMAGE SYSPCH  FILE ON DISK (81-BYTE
                                     17 *        RECORDS), CONTAINING EXACTLY ONE RELOCATABLE MODULE.  THIS
                                     18 *        FILE IS TYPICALLY SYSPCH OUTPUT FROM THE RSERV PROGRAM.
                                     19 *   CARDS, SYS004, REP CARDS TO BE ADDED JUST BEFORE THE RELOCATABLE
                                     20 *        MODULE'S END CARD.  EACH CARD STARTS '+REP' AND OTHERWISE
                                     21 *        FOLLOWS THE REP CARD FORMAT DOCUMENTED IN DOS SYSTEM CONTROL
                                     22 *        AND SERVICE, GC24-5036.  SEE P. 233 OF THE -7 EDITION.
                                     23 *
                                     24 * OUTPUT
                                     25 *   UOUT, SYS005, UNBLOCKED CARD IMAGE SYSIPT FILE ON DISK (80-BYTE
                                     26 *        RECORDS).  THIS FILE A COPY OF THE INPUT FILE, WITH REP CARDS
                                     27 *        FROM THE CARD READER ADDED JUST BEFORE THE END CARD.  THE
                                     28 *        STACKER SELECTION BYTE IN COLUMN ONE IS REMOVED--COLUMNS 2-81
                                     29 *        OF THE INPUT ARE PLACED IN 1-80 OF THE OUTPUT.  ANY REP CARDS
                                     30 *        IN THE INPUT ARE REMOVED.  (SHOULD ONE WISH TO KEEP THEM,
                                     31 *        INCLUDE THEM IN THE CARD INPUT STREAM.)  NOTE THAT THE '+' IN
                                     32 *        THE REP CARD INPUT CARDS IS CHANGED TO X'02' BEFORE BEING
                                     33 *        WRITTEN.
                                     34 *
                                     35 ***********************************************************************


 
                                     37 ***********************************************************************
                                     38 *
                                     39 *
000000                               40 ZAPRELO  START 0
000000 05C0                          41          BALR  12,0                     LOAD BASE REG
000002 06C0                          42          BCTR  12,0
000004 06C0                          43          BCTR  12,0
000000                               44          USING ZAPRELO,12
                                     45 *
                                     46          OPEN  UIN,UOUT            OPEN INPUT AND OUTPUT FILES
                                     47+* 360N-CL-453 OPEN     CHANGE LEVEL 3-3                             3-3
000006 0700                          48+         CNOP  0,4
000008                               49+         DC    0F'0'
000008 4110 C1F0            001F0    50+         LA    1,=C'$$BOPEN '

ZAPR   APPLY REP CARDS TO RELOCATABLE MODULE                                                                   PAGE    2


  LOC  OBJECT CODE    ADDR1 ADDR2  STMT   SOURCE STATEMENT                                          FDOS CL3-10 03/31/70

00000C 4500 C018            00018    51+IJJO0001 BAL   0,*+4+4*(3-1)
000010 00000228                      52+         DC    A(UIN)
000014 000002B0                      53+         DC    A(UOUT)
000018 0A02                          54+         SVC   2
                                     55 *
                                     56 *  COPY INPUT TO OUTFILE UNTIL END CARD READ.
                                     57 *
00001A                               58 READLOOP DS    0H                  LOOP UNTIL RELO MOD 'END' CARD
                                     59          GET   UIN                 READ A CARD
                                     60+* 360N-CL-453 GET      CHANGE LEVEL 3-0
00001A 5810 C200            00200    61+         L     1,=A(UIN) GET DTF TABLE ADDRESS
00001E 58F1 0010            00010    62+         L     15,16(1) GET LOGIC MODULE ADDRESS
000022 45EF 0008            00008    63+         BAL   14,8(15) BRANCH TO GET ROUTINE
000026 D503 C0E5 C1DD 000E5 001DD    64          CLC   INCARD(L'ENDTEST),ENDTEST  IS IT AN END CARD
00002C 4780 C050            00050    65          BE    REPLOOP             ..YES, GO GET REP CARDS
000030 D505 C0E5 C1E4 000E5 001E4    66          CLC   INCARD(L'REPTEST1),REPTEST1 IS IT A REP CARD
000036 4780 C01A            0001A    67          BE    READLOOP            ..YES, DROP IT
00003A D24F C13D C0E5 0013D 000E5    68          MVC   OUTCARD,INCARD      COPY TO OUTPUT
                                     69          PUT   UOUT                WRITE CARD TO SYSPCH
                                     70+* 360N-CL-453 PUT          CHANGE LEVEL 3-5                         3-5
000040 5810 C204            00204    71+         L     1,=A(UOUT) GET DTF TABLE ADDRESS
000044 58F1 0010            00010    72+         L     15,16(1) GET LOGIC MODULE ADDRESS     3-5
000048 45EF 000C            0000C    73+         BAL   14,12(15) BRANCH TO PUT ROUTINE        3-5
00004C 47F0 C01A            0001A    74          B     READLOOP            CONTINUE COPYING
                                     75 *
                                     76 * RELO MODULE 'END' CARD READ.  COPY REP CARDS UNTIL EOF
                                     77 *
000050                               78 REPLOOP  DS    0H                  COPY REP CARDS LOOP
                                     79          EXCP  INREPS              READ A CARD
                                     80+* 360N-CL-453 EXCP     CHANGE LEVEL 3-0
000050 5810 C208            00208    81+         L     1,=A(INREPS)
000054 0A00                          82+         SVC   0
                                     83          WAIT  (1)                 WAIT FOR COMPLETION
                                     84+* 360N-CL-453 WAIT     CHANGE LEVEL 3-0
000056 9180 1002      00002          85+         TM    2(1),X'80'
00005A 4710 C060            00060    86+         BO    *+6
00005E 0A07                          87+         SVC   7
000060 9101 1004      00004          88          TM    4(1),X'01'          UNIT EXCEPTION RAISED
000064 4710 C096            00096    89          BO    REPDONE             ..YES, END OF DECK, DONE
000068 D502 C18D C1E1 0018D 001E1    90          CLC   REPCARD(L'EOFTEST),EOFTEST  END OF FILE (/*)
00006E 4780 C096            00096    91          BE    REPDONE             ..YES, END OF DECK, DONE
000072 D503 C18D C1EA 0018D 001EA    92          CLC   REPCARD(L'REPTEST2),REPTEST2  +REP CARD
000078 4770 C050            00050    93          BNE   REPLOOP             ..NO, SKIP/IGNORE IT
00007C D24F C13D C18D 0013D 0018D    94          MVC   OUTCARD,REPCARD     COPY TO OUTPUT
000082 9202 C13D      0013D          95          MVI   OUTCARD,X'02'       CREATE 12-2-9 MULTIPUNCH
                                     96          PUT   UOUT                WRITE CARD TO SYSPCH
                                     97+* 360N-CL-453 PUT          CHANGE LEVEL 3-5                         3-5
000086 5810 C204            00204    98+         L     1,=A(UOUT) GET DTF TABLE ADDRESS
00008A 58F1 0010            00010    99+         L     15,16(1) GET LOGIC MODULE ADDRESS     3-5
00008E 45EF 000C            0000C   100+         BAL   14,12(15) BRANCH TO PUT ROUTINE        3-5
000092 47F0 C050            00050   101          B     REPLOOP             CONTINUE COPYING

ZAPR   APPLY REP CARDS TO RELOCATABLE MODULE                                                                   PAGE    3


  LOC  OBJECT CODE    ADDR1 ADDR2  STMT   SOURCE STATEMENT                                          FDOS CL3-10 03/31/70

                                    102 *
                                    103 * EOF ON SYS000, END OF REP CARDS,  WRITE END CARD AND EXIT
                                    104 *
000096                              105 REPDONE  DS    0H                  END OF REP CARDS
000096 D24F C13D C0E5 0013D 000E5   106          MVC   OUTCARD,INCARD      COPY TO OUTPUT
                                    107          PUT   UOUT                WRITE CARD TO SYSPCH
                                    108+* 360N-CL-453 PUT          CHANGE LEVEL 3-5                         3-5
00009C 5810 C204            00204   109+         L     1,=A(UOUT) GET DTF TABLE ADDRESS
0000A0 58F1 0010            00010   110+         L     15,16(1) GET LOGIC MODULE ADDRESS     3-5
0000A4 45EF 000C            0000C   111+         BAL   14,12(15) BRANCH TO PUT ROUTINE        3-5
                                    112 *
                                    113 * END CARD PROCESSED.  DUPLICATE THE REST OF THE DECK
                                    114 *
0000A8                              115 ENDLOOP  DS    0H                  READ REMAINDER OF DECK
                                    116          GET   UIN                 READ NEXT CARD
                                    117+* 360N-CL-453 GET      CHANGE LEVEL 3-0
0000A8 5810 C200            00200   118+         L     1,=A(UIN) GET DTF TABLE ADDRESS
0000AC 58F1 0010            00010   119+         L     15,16(1) GET LOGIC MODULE ADDRESS
0000B0 45EF 0008            00008   120+         BAL   14,8(15) BRANCH TO GET ROUTINE
0000B4 D24F C13D C0E5 0013D 000E5   121          MVC   OUTCARD,INCARD      COPY TO OUTPUT
                                    122          PUT   UOUT                WRITE IT
                                    123+* 360N-CL-453 PUT          CHANGE LEVEL 3-5                         3-5
0000BA 5810 C204            00204   124+         L     1,=A(UOUT) GET DTF TABLE ADDRESS
0000BE 58F1 0010            00010   125+         L     15,16(1) GET LOGIC MODULE ADDRESS     3-5
0000C2 45EF 000C            0000C   126+         BAL   14,12(15) BRANCH TO PUT ROUTINE        3-5
0000C6 47F0 C0A8            000A8   127          B     ENDLOOP             CONTINUE THE COPY
                                    128 *
                                    129 * EOF.  WRITE AN EOF, CLOSE FILES AND EXIT.
                                    130 *
0000CA                              131 ENDINPUT DS    0H
0000CA D202 C13D C1E1 0013D 001E1   132          MVC   OUTCARD(L'EOFTEST),EOFTEST MOVE '/* '
                                    133          CLOSE UIN,UOUT            CLOSE FILES
                                    134+* 360N-CL-453 CLOSE    CHANGE LEVEL 3-3                             3-3
0000D0                              135+         CNOP  0,4
0000D0                              136+         DC    0F'0'
0000D0 4110 C1F8            001F8   137+         LA    1,=C'$$BCLOSE'

// JOB SYSGEN8B   $$BDITFP  DITTO FILE PROTECT TRANSIENT                00.30.59
// OPTION CATAL,LOG                                                     $$FP0002
   PHASE $$BDITFP,+0                                                    $$FP0003
// EXEC ASSEMBLY                                                        $$FP0004
 

                                              EXTERNAL SYMBOL DICTIONARY                                       PAGE    1

          PC  01 000000 0000C8

                                                                                                               PAGE    1


  LOC  OBJECT CODE    ADDR1 ADDR2  STMT   SOURCE STATEMENT                                          FDOS CL3-10 03/31/70

                                      2 *********************************************************************** $$FP0006
                                      3 *                                                                     * $$FP0007
                                      4 *        THIS  B-TRANSIENT IS FETCHED BY THE PROBLEM PROGRAM 'DITTO', * $$FP0008
                                      5 *        TO LOAD DISK FILE EXTENTS WHEN OPERATING IN A FILE PROTECTED * $$FP0009
                                      6 *        ENVIRONMENT. THESE EXTENTS WILL BE DEQUED BY JOB CONTROL     * $$FP0010
                                      7 *        AT EOJ TIME.                                                 * $$FP0011
                                      8 *        INFORMATION PASSED TO THE TRANSIENT:                         * $$FP0012
                                      9 *             REG  0  POINTS TO AN 8 BYTE PASS FIELD:                 * $$FP0013
                                     10 *                  FIELD BYTE 0-3 = ADDRESS OF THE DESIRED LUB        * $$FP0014
                                     11 *                  FIELD BYTE 4-7 = FILE MASK  (LIMITS AND            * $$FP0015
                                     12 *                   PARTITION OWNERSHIP CODE).                        * $$FP0016
                                     13 *        INFORMATION RETURNED TO DITTO:                               * $$FP0017
                                     14 *             HEX FF RETURN TO BYTE 0 OF THE FILE MASK IF NO          * $$FP0018
                                     15 *                   JIBS ARE AVAILABLE.                               * $$FP0019
                                     16 *        PROCEDURE:                                                   * $$FP0020
                                     17 *             1. CHECK LUB FOR AN ATTACHED JIB.                       * $$FP0021
                                     18 *             2. IF NONE, OBTAIN AND ATTACH JIB AND LOAD XTENTS IN JIB* $$FP0022
                                     19 *             3. IF JIB IS ATTACHED, FOLLOW JIB CHAIN UNTIL XTENT TYPE* $$FP0023
                                     20 *                LOCATED OR END OF CHAIN REACHED.                     * $$FP0024
                                     21 *             4. IF XTENT TYPE, INCREASE LIMITS TO MAXIMUM.           * $$FP0025
                                     22 *             5. IF END OF CHAIN, ATTACH JIB AND LOAD XTENTS.         * $$FP0026
                                     23 *                                                                     * $$FP0027
                                     24 *              C. A. ALEXANDER     IBM     DETROIT, MICHIGAN          * $$FP0028
                                     25 *********************************************************************** $$FP0029

000020 4630 F024            00024    36          BCT   3,*+4               LUB RESEMBLE A JIB.                  $$FP0040

* DEBLOCK POWER TO SCRATCH TAPE, 1 FILE
// ASSGN SYS004,X'280'                  INPUT TAPE

// EXEC TPTP
 

// UTT TRF,FF,A=(81,3240),B=(80,80),IR,OR
// FS 2,80,1
// END

OUTPUT RECORD LENGTH  0080

OUTPUT BLOCK LENGTH 00080

2 INPUT,2 OUTPUT AREAS ASSIGNED
RECORD FORMAT FIXED
TYPE REBLOCK, FIELD SELECT

BLOCK NO. 000168,.INPUT AREA UNDERFLOW
8001D IS IT 
REPLY Y
NUMBER OF INPUT BLOCKS PROCESSED  000168
NUMBER OF OUTPUT BLOCKS PROCESSED 006684
END OF JOB

                                      4 *              IAG=NO,             UNKNOWN POWER MACRO OPERAND
                                      5 *
                                      6 * DBLK=920,    7 RECS/TRK, 88% TRACK UTILIZATION
                                      7 * TRACKGP=2    2 TRACKS/GROUP
                                      8 * NTRKGRP=500  NTRKGRP * TRACKGP = D FILE TRACKS = 1000 (50 CYL)
                                      9 * MAXJOBS=110  Q FILE RECS = MAXJOBS + 1 (FOR THE Q FILE MASTER REC)
                                     10 *                 110 + 1 = 111 RECORDS IN Q FILE
                                     11 *
                                     12 * Q FILE RECSIZE = MAX(MASTER RECORD SIZE, DATA RECORD SIZE)
                                     13 *
                                     14 * MASTER RECORD SIZE = 208 + (32 * NUMPARTS)
                                     15 *                    = 208 + (32 * 2)
                                     16 *                    = 272
                                     17 *    (NUMPARTS IS NUMBER OF PARTITIONS POWER WILL SUPPORT)

                                   1567+*
                                   1568+* THIS ROUTINE IS USED TO FIND THE NEXT PARAMETER IN AN OPERAND FIELD.
                                   1569+* IF CALLER ENTERS AT GETOPRND, THIS ROUTINE SEARCHES FOR FIRST NON-
                                   1570+* BLANK.  IF CALLER ENTERS AT GETPARAM, SARG MUST POINT TO A NON-BLANK
                                   1571+*   THE CALLER MUST:  1. PASS RETURN ADDRESS IN REG 2
                                   1572+*                     2. PASS SARG ADDRESS IN REG 3
                                   1573+*                     3. PASS ADDRESS OF END OF FIELD + 1 IN REG 4
                                   1574+*
                                   1575+*   THIS ROUTINE WILL :  1. RETURN ALL REGS EXCEPT 3 & 5 UNCHANGED
                                   1576+*                        2. PLACE ACTUAL LENGTH OF PARAMETER IN REG 5
                                   1577+*                           IF SARG POINTS TO A COMMA, REG 5 IS ZERO
                                   1578+*                        3. REG 3 POINTS TO THE PARAMETER OR COMMA
                                   1579+*                        4. RETURN VIA REG 2 WHEN FIELD WAS EXHAUSTED
                                   1580+*                        5. RETURN VIA REG 2 + 4 WHEN SARG POINTS TO A
                                   1581+*                           COMMA
                                   1582+*                        6. RETURN VIA REG 2 + 8 WHEN SARG HAS FOUND
                                   1583+*                           THE PARAMETER
                                   1584+*
00211E 9540 3000      00000        1585+GETOPRND CLI   0(R3),X'40' .        IS CHARACTER A BLANK
002122 4770 8382            02132  1586+         BNE   GETPARAM .          BRANCH IF NO
002126 4133 0001            00001  1587+         LA    R3,1(R3) .            INCREMENT TO NEXT CHARACTER

  21- 1  IJS063I W ALIGNMENT       TO ALIGN BLOCKED RECORDS ADD 4 BYTES TO THE 01 CONTAINING DATANAME SALARY-RECORD.

00042   032015      02 FILLER PIC X(34) VALUE SPACES.                           $4820042
00043   032020   01 DSPY.                                                       $4820043
00044   032030      02 FILLER    PIC X(40)     VALUE SPACES.                    $4820044
00045   032040      02 PRSNT     PIC A(33).                                     $4820045
00046   032045      02 FILLER PIC X(27) VALUE SPACES.                           $4820046
00047   032050   01 PG-HDING.                                                   $4820047
00048   032060      02 FILLER    PIC X(46)     VALUE SPACES.                    $4820048
00049   032070      02 WEEKLY    PIC A(6)      VALUE 'WEEKLY'.                  $4820049
00050   032080      02 FILLER    PIC X(3)      VALUE SPACES.                    $4820050
00051   032090      02 MONTHLY   PIC A(7)      VALUE 'MONTHLY'.                 $4820051
00052   032100      02 FILLER    PIC X(3)      VALUE SPACES.                    $4820052
00053   032110      02 ANNUAL    PIC A(6)      VALUE 'ANNUAL'.                  $4820053

     2


00054   032120      02 FILLER    PIC X(29)     VALUE SPACES.                    $4820054
00055   040130                                                                  $4820055
00056   040140 PROCEDURE DIVISION.                                              $4820056
00057   040150   START-PROG.                                                    $4820057
00058   040160     OPEN OUTPUT SALARY-FILE.                                     $4820058
00059   040170     WRITE SALARY-RECORD FROM PG-HDING AFTER ADVANCING 0 LINES.   $4820059
00060   040180     PERFORM CALCULATIONS                                         $4820060
00061   040190       VARYING MONTHLY-PAY FROM 500 BY 10                         $4820061
00062   040200       UNTIL MONTHLY-PAY IS GREATER THAN 1000.                    $4820062
00063   041010     IF TOTAL-A = CON-A AND TOTAL-B = CON-B AND TOTAL-C = CON-C   $4820063
00064   041020         MOVE 'TABLE VALUES ARE CORRECT' TO SHOW                  $4820064
00065   041030         WRITE SALARY-RECORD FROM MESG AFTER ADVANCING 2 LINES    $4820065
00066   041040       ELSE                                                       $4820066
00067   041050         MOVE 'TABLE VALUES ARE NOT CORRECT' TO PRSNT             $4820067
00068   041060         WRITE SALARY-RECORD FROM DSPY AFTER ADVANCING 2 LINES.   $4820068
00069   041070     CLOSE SALARY-FILE.                                           $4820069
00070   041080     STOP RUN.                                                    $4820070
00071   041090   CALCULATIONS.                                                  $4820071
00072   041100     COMPUTE WEEKLY-PAY = 3 * MONTHLY-PAY / 13.                   $4820072
00073   041110     COMPUTE ANNUAL-PAY = 12 * MONTHLY-PAY.                       $4820073
00074   041120     MOVE WEEKLY-PAY TO WEEKLY IN SALARIES.                       $4820074
00075   041130     MOVE MONTHLY-PAY TO MONTHLY IN SALARIES.                     $4820075
00076   041140     MOVE ANNUAL-PAY TO ANNUAL IN SALARIES.                       $4820076
00077   041150     ADD WEEKLY-PAY TO TOTAL-A.                                   $4820077
00078   041160     ADD MONTHLY-PAY TO TOTAL-B.                                  $4820078
00079   041170     ADD ANNUAL-PAY TO TOTAL-C.                                   $4820079
00080   041180     WRITE SALARY-RECORD FROM SALARIES AFTER ADVANCING 1 LINES.   $4820080

// JOB VERPLI01                                                         00.02.06
// OPTION LINK
// EXEC PL/I
 

         DOS PL/I COMPILER  360N-PL-464 CL3-13             VERPLI01            03/26/70            PAGE 001


                                                    O P T I O N S  L I S T

* PROCESS STMT

OPTIONS TAKEN ARE 60C,LIST,XREF,ERRS,OPT,STMT.

         DOS PL/I COMPILER  360N-PL-464 CL3-13             VERPLI01            03/26/70            PAGE 002


 /*PL/I SAMPLE PROGRAM FOR DOS/TOS */

                     /*PL/I SAMPLE PROGRAM FOR DOS/TOS */
     1               PL1: PROCEDURE OPTIONS (MAIN);
     2                         DECLARE  ( X, INITVALUE, TERMVALUE, STEP, A(5), B(2) )
                                        FLOAT BINARY (21) ;
                     /*********************************** 
                        THIS PROGRAM COMPUTES A SMALL TABLE CONTAINING A FEW MATH FUNCTIONS
 
                        INPUT DATA.. INITVALUE - START POINT OF TABLE
                                     TERMVALUE   - TERMVALUE POINT TABLE
                                     STEP  - STEP WIDTH IN TABLE
 
                        THE ABSOLUTE VALUES OF INITVALUE AND TERMVALUE MAY NOT BE GREATER
                        THAN  999.999, THE ABSOLUTE VALUE OF STEP MAY NOT BE LESS THAN
                        0.001.
 
                        BASED ON THE IBM SUPPLIED SAMPLE PL/I INSTALLATION VERIFICATION
                        PROGRAM, BUT RE-CODED TO USE MODERN STRUCTURED PROGRAMMING
                        TECHNIQUES.
 
                     ******************************************************************* */
 
     3                         GET EDIT (INITVALUE, TERMVALUE, STEP)(3 F(8,3)) ;
 
     4                         PUT EDIT ('X     SQRT(X**2+1)      X**2','X**3','SIN(X)
                      COS(X)      SQRT(X)     SQRT(X**3)') (X(4),A(41),A(14),A(61)) ;
 
     5                         IF (ABS(INITVALUE) < 1000.) & (ABS(STEP) >= .001)
                                  THEN DO X=INITVALUE TO TERMVALUE+STEP/1E3 BY STEP ;
     6                                  A(2)=X*X ;
     7                                  A(1)=SQRT(A(2)+1);
     8                                  A(3)=A(2)*X  ;
     9                                  A(4)=SIN(X) ;
    10                                  A(5)=COS(X) ;
    11                                  PUT EDIT (X,A) (F(8,3),F(13,3),2 E(16,5),2 F(13,6));
    12                                  IF X < 0
                                           THEN PUT EDIT ('--','--') (X(7), A(15), A(19)) ;
    13                                     ELSE BEGIN ;
    14                                        B(1)=SQRT(X)    ;
    15                                        B(2)=SQRT(A(3)) ;
    16                                        PUT EDIT (B,' ') (F(12,4), E(16,5),A(13)) ;
    17                                     END ;
    18                               END  /* DO LOOP */ ;
    19                            ELSE BEGIN ;
    20                               PUT EDIT ('INPUT DATA ERROR') (A(16)) ;
    21                               STOP /* END ON WRONG INPUT */ ;
    22                               END ;
 
    23                         PUT SKIP EDIT (' NORMAL END')(A);
    24                         RETURN;/* NORMAL END */ ;
    26                         END  /* TABLE */  ;

         DOS PL/I COMPILER  360N-PL-464 CL3-13             VERPLI01            03/26/70            PAGE 003
